editorialNotes.short: Your child’s unique world—in words, sounds and images.
See internal organs in action: lungs breathe, muscles bend and nerves respond to a pinprick.

editorialNotes.standard: Ever pondered the atomic weight of Bismuth? Do you debate the density of Niobium over dinner? If so, this app is for you. Chemistry truly comes to life with this fully interactive version of the periodic table. Engage with the elements like never before and witness the wonders of science in beautiful detail.
editorialNotes.short: Chemistry comes to life with this interactive version of the periodic table.

editorialNotes.standard: Slide a shape into the correct hole—easy, right? It is, at first. But what makes Busy Shapes so clever is the way it gently gets more challenging, motivating little kids to find solutions to each puzzle through experimentation. From shape-changing to colour-mixing to hidden holes, we’re impressed with how the gameplay spurs out-of-the-box thinking, stimulating curious young minds.
